parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of Takata airbag recall parts can lead to a delay in repair, leaving drivers and passengers at risk of injury or death due to the faulty airbags.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the coolant valley seal can cause coolant leaks, leading to engine overheating, damage to engine components, and potentially resulting in engine failure or stalling, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Low coolant level in the reservoir
coolant leaks around the transmission bell housing
dry coolant spots around the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Brake Booster or Master Cylinder
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty brake booster or master cylinder can cause a loss of braking power, leading to increased stopping distances, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: A buzzing or squealing noise is heard when applying the brake pedal
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the electric stability control system is difficult to use.
